                                        1252,
                                        2339,
                                        2301,
                                        2781
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "Starting from the CSH dataset, we applied the interval PLSDA (iPLS- DA) algorithm [52] to calculate image- level classification models and select relevant spatial features ascribable to the presence of punctures. Then, we visualized back the selected features of interest into the original image domain, allowing to automatically select ROIs ascribable to punctured areas; this procedure will be referred to as image reconstruction. Fig. 8 shows a schematic representation of such a supervised annotation method."
                                }
                            ]
                        }
